articles.title: Western Australia records first monkeypox case in returned overseas traveller - ABC News
articles.description: Overseas travellers returning to Western Australia are urged to monitor for symptoms of monkeypox after the state records its first case.
articles.content:
Western Australia has detected its first case of monkeypox in a traveller returning to the state from overseas. Key points:
  • The person is in isolation and contact tracing is underway
